Below is a copy/paste runbook. Only edit the first block.

This matches your uploaded Sensu ARM64 migration notes: assets first, then image/scheduling, then ArgoCD sync and validation.  Sensu assets should use url, sha512, and architecture filters such as entity.system.arch == 'arm64'; Kubernetes exposes node architecture with kubernetes.io/arch; and argocd app wait waits for sync/health. 


---

0. Edit this block only

cat > sensu-arm64-vars.sh <<'EOF'
export AWS_REGION="<aws-region>"
export EKS_CLUSTER="<eks-cluster-name>"

export REPO_DIR="$HOME/<path-to-your-sensu-git-repo>"
export STG_BRANCH="STG"

export NS="<sensu-namespace>"
export ARGO_APP="<argocd-sensu-app-name>"

export BACKEND_STS="sensu-backend"
export AGENT_DS="sensu-agent"

export ASSET_DIR="sensu-go/base/asset"
export KUSTOMIZE_OVERLAY="sensu-go/overlays/stg"

# Current image name as written in Kubernetes YAML, without tag if possible.
# Example: 123456789.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/sensu
export CURRENT_SENSU_IMAGE_NAME="<current-sensu-image-name>"

# New ARM64 or multi-arch Sensu image.
# Example: sensu/sensu:6.14.0
export SENSU_IMAGE="<new-arm64-or-multiarch-sensu-image>:<tag>"

# Leave these as-is if your Graviton nodes use this taint.
# If your Graviton nodes are not tainted, this toleration is harmless.
export GRAVITON_TAINT_KEY="graviton"
export GRAVITON_TAINT_VALUE="true"
EOF

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh


---

1. Login to EKS and check tools

set -euo pipefail
source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

for cmd in aws kubectl argocd git docker kustomize; do
  command -v "$cmd" >/dev/null 2>&1 || {
    echo "STOP: Missing command: $cmd"
    exit 1
  }
done

aws eks update-kubeconfig \
  --region "$AWS_REGION" \
  --name "$EKS_CLUSTER"

kubectl config current-context

argocd app get "$ARGO_APP"


---

2. Confirm Graviton/ARM64 nodes exist

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

kubectl get nodes -L kubernetes.io/arch

ARM64_NODE_COUNT="$(kubectl get nodes -l kubernetes.io/arch=arm64 --no-headers 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')"

echo "ARM64 node count: $ARM64_NODE_COUNT"

if [ "$ARM64_NODE_COUNT" -eq 0 ]; then
  echo "STOP: No ARM64 nodes found. Add Graviton nodes before continuing."
  exit 1
fi

kubectl get nodes -l kubernetes.io/arch=arm64 -o wide


---

3. Checkout STG branch

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

cd "$REPO_DIR"

git fetch origin
git checkout "$STG_BRANCH"
git pull --ff-only origin "$STG_BRANCH"

if [ -n "$(git status --porcelain)" ]; then
  echo "STOP: Git repo has uncommitted changes. Commit/stash them first."
  git status --short
  exit 1
fi


---

4. Backup current live Sensu state

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

mkdir -p /tmp/sensu-arm64-backup

kubectl get sts "$BACKEND_STS" -n "$NS" -o yaml \
  > /tmp/sensu-arm64-backup/backend-before.yaml

kubectl get ds "$AGENT_DS" -n "$NS" -o yaml \
  > /tmp/sensu-arm64-backup/agent-before.yaml

kubectl get pods -n "$NS" -o wide \
  > /tmp/sensu-arm64-backup/pods-before.txt

kubectl get nodes -L kubernetes.io/arch \
  > /tmp/sensu-arm64-backup/nodes-before.txt

sensuctl asset list --format yaml \
  > /tmp/sensu-arm64-backup/assets-before.yaml || true

echo "Backup written to /tmp/sensu-arm64-backup"


---

5. Audit Sensu assets

Run this before changing nodes to ARM64.

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

cd "$REPO_DIR"

echo "Checking asset directory:"
ls -la "$ASSET_DIR"

echo
echo "Assets missing ARM64 filter:"
MISSING_ARM64="$(
  find "$ASSET_DIR" -type f \( -name "*.yml" -o -name "*.yaml" \) -print0 \
  | xargs -0 grep -L "entity.system.arch == 'arm64'" || true
)"

if [ -n "$MISSING_ARM64" ]; then
  echo "$MISSING_ARM64"
  echo
  echo "STOP: Some asset files do not contain ARM64 filters."
  echo "Fix these files before continuing."
  exit 1
else
  echo "OK: All asset files contain ARM64 filter text."
fi

echo
echo "Checking for risky filters: null:"
BAD_FILTERS="$(grep -R "filters: null" "$ASSET_DIR" || true)"

if [ -n "$BAD_FILTERS" ]; then
  echo "$BAD_FILTERS"
  echo
  echo "STOP: filters: null found. This can make AMD64 assets run on ARM64."
  echo "Fix these before continuing."
  exit 1
else
  echo "OK: No filters: null found."
fi

echo
echo "Checking for missing sha512:"
NO_SHA="$(
  find "$ASSET_DIR" -type f \( -name "*.yml" -o -name "*.yaml" \) -print0 \
  | xargs -0 grep -L "sha512:" || true
)"

if [ -n "$NO_SHA" ]; then
  echo "$NO_SHA"
  echo
  echo "STOP: Some asset files do not contain sha512."
  echo "Fix these before continuing."
  exit 1
else
  echo "OK: sha512 found in all asset files."
fi

echo
echo "Runtime asset references:"
grep -R "runtime_assets:" -n sensu-go || true


---

6. Generate SHA512 for any missing ARM64 tarball

Only run this when you are adding a new ARM64 asset URL.

export ARM64_ASSET_URL="<paste-arm64-tar-gz-url-here>"
export ARM64_ASSET_FILE="/tmp/$(basename "$ARM64_ASSET_URL")"

curl -fL "$ARM64_ASSET_URL" -o "$ARM64_ASSET_FILE"

sha512sum "$ARM64_ASSET_FILE"

Copy the checksum output into the asset YAML like this:

sha512: <sha512-value>
filters:
  - entity.system.os == 'linux'
  - entity.system.arch == 'arm64'

Then rerun section 5.


---

7. Verify Sensu image supports ARM64

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

if echo "$SENSU_IMAGE" | grep -q ".dkr.ecr."; then
  ECR_REGISTRY="$(echo "$SENSU_IMAGE" | cut -d/ -f1)"
  aws ecr get-login-password --region "$AWS_REGION" \
    | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin "$ECR_REGISTRY"
fi

docker buildx imagetools inspect "$SENSU_IMAGE" \
  > /tmp/sensu-image-manifest.txt

cat /tmp/sensu-image-manifest.txt | grep -E "linux/(amd64|arm64)" || true

grep -q "linux/arm64" /tmp/sensu-image-manifest.txt || {
  echo "STOP: Sensu image does not show linux/arm64."
  exit 1
}

echo "OK: Sensu image supports linux/arm64."


---

8. Create ARM64 Kustomize patches

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

cd "$REPO_DIR/$KUSTOMIZE_OVERLAY"

mkdir -p patches

cat > patches/sensu-backend-arm64.yaml <<EOF
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: StatefulSet
metadata:
  name: ${BACKEND_STS}
spec:
  template:
    spec:
      nodeSelector:
        kubernetes.io/arch: arm64
      tolerations:
        - key: ${GRAVITON_TAINT_KEY}
          operator: Equal
          value: "${GRAVITON_TAINT_VALUE}"
          effect: NoSchedule
EOF

cat > patches/sensu-agent-arm64.yaml <<EOF
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: DaemonSet
metadata:
  name: ${AGENT_DS}
spec:
  template:
    spec:
      nodeSelector:
        kubernetes.io/arch: arm64
      tolerations:
        - key: ${GRAVITON_TAINT_KEY}
          operator: Equal
          value: "${GRAVITON_TAINT_VALUE}"
          effect: NoSchedule
EOF

kustomize edit add patch --path patches/sensu-backend-arm64.yaml || true
kustomize edit add patch --path patches/sensu-agent-arm64.yaml || true

kustomize edit set image "${CURRENT_SENSU_IMAGE_NAME}=${SENSU_IMAGE}"


---

9. Render manifests locally and confirm ARM64 is present

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

cd "$REPO_DIR/$KUSTOMIZE_OVERLAY"

kustomize build . > /tmp/sensu-arm64-rendered.yaml

grep -n "kubernetes.io/arch: arm64" /tmp/sensu-arm64-rendered.yaml

grep -n "$SENSU_IMAGE" /tmp/sensu-arm64-rendered.yaml || {
  echo "STOP: New Sensu image not found in rendered YAML."
  exit 1
}

echo "OK: Rendered YAML contains ARM64 scheduling and new image."


---

10. Commit and push to STG

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

cd "$REPO_DIR"

git status --short
git diff -- "$ASSET_DIR" "$KUSTOMIZE_OVERLAY" || true

git add "$ASSET_DIR" "$KUSTOMIZE_OVERLAY"

git commit -m "Migrate Sensu STG to ARM64 Graviton"

git push origin "$STG_BRANCH"


---

11. Sync with ArgoCD

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

argocd app diff "$ARGO_APP" || true

argocd app sync "$ARGO_APP"

argocd app wait "$ARGO_APP" \
  --sync \
  --health \
  --timeout 600


---

12. Wait for Kubernetes rollout

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

kubectl rollout status sts/"$BACKEND_STS" -n "$NS" --timeout=600s

kubectl rollout status ds/"$AGENT_DS" -n "$NS" --timeout=600s

kubectl get pods -n "$NS" -o wide


---

13. Confirm Sensu pods are on ARM64 nodes

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

kubectl get pods -n "$NS" -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}{" "}{.spec.nodeName}{"\n"}{end}' \
  | grep -E "${BACKEND_STS}|${AGENT_DS}|sensu" \
  > /tmp/sensu-pod-nodes.txt || true

cat /tmp/sensu-pod-nodes.txt

echo
echo "Node architecture for Sensu pods:"

while read -r POD NODE; do
  ARCH="$(kubectl get node "$NODE" -o jsonpath='{.metadata.labels.kubernetes\.io/arch}')"
  echo "$POD -> $NODE -> $ARCH"
done < /tmp/sensu-pod-nodes.txt

Expected output should show:

arm64


---

14. Confirm inside containers

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

for POD in $(kubectl get pods -n "$NS" -o name | grep -E "${BACKEND_STS}|${AGENT_DS}|sensu" | sed 's#pod/##'); do
  echo "===== $POD ====="
  kubectl exec -n "$NS" "$POD" -- uname -m || true
done

Expected output on ARM64 is usually:

aarch64


---

15. Verify Sensu assets after sync

sensuctl asset list --format yaml \
  | grep -E "name:|url:|sha512:|amd64|arm64" || true


---

16. Verify Sensu entities and events

sensuctl entity list

sensuctl event list


---

17. Check backend logs

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

kubectl logs -n "$NS" sts/"$BACKEND_STS" --tail=300 \
  | grep -Ei "error|failed|exec format|no matching asset|sha512|ruby|permission denied" || true

Good result:

no output


---

18. Check agent logs

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

kubectl logs -n "$NS" ds/"$AGENT_DS" --tail=300 \
  | grep -Ei "error|failed|exec format|no matching asset|sha512|ruby|permission denied" || true

Good result:

no output


---

19. Check Kubernetes events

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

kubectl get events -n "$NS" --sort-by=.lastTimestamp | tail -80

Look for bad signs:

ImagePullBackOff
CrashLoopBackOff
FailedScheduling
exec format error


---

20. Final success check

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

echo "Pods:"
kubectl get pods -n "$NS" -o wide

echo
echo "Sensu entities:"
sensuctl entity list

echo
echo "Sensu events:"
sensuctl event list

echo
echo "Recent backend errors:"
kubectl logs -n "$NS" sts/"$BACKEND_STS" --tail=200 \
  | grep -Ei "error|failed|exec format|no matching asset|sha512|ruby|permission denied" || true

echo
echo "Recent agent errors:"
kubectl logs -n "$NS" ds/"$AGENT_DS" --tail=200 \
  | grep -Ei "error|failed|exec format|no matching asset|sha512|ruby|permission denied" || true

Migration is complete only when:

Pods are Running
Pods are on arm64 nodes
sensuctl asset list shows arm64 builds
sensuctl event list looks normal
No exec format error
No no matching asset build
No sha512 mismatch
No ruby not found


---

Rollback command

Run this only if STG fails.

source sensu-arm64-vars.sh

cd "$REPO_DIR"

git revert HEAD --no-edit
git push origin "$STG_BRANCH"

argocd app sync "$ARGO_APP"

argocd app wait "$ARGO_APP" \
  --sync \
  --health \
  --timeout 600

kubectl rollout status sts/"$BACKEND_STS" -n "$NS" --timeout=600s
kubectl rollout status ds/"$AGENT_DS" -n "$NS" --timeout=600s

kubectl get pods -n "$NS" -o wide

Do not run this in production until STG passes with clean Sensu events and clean backend/agent logs.